# =============================================================================
# .trivyignore — Trivy vulnerability suppression list
# =============================================================================
# Add CVE IDs (one per line) below to suppress specific findings that have
# been reviewed, accepted, or are not applicable to this project.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN          # plain CVE suppression
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN exp:2026-12-31  # suppression with an expiry date
#
# Guidelines:
#   - Always add a comment explaining WHY a finding is suppressed.
#   - Use expiry dates (exp:YYYY-MM-DD) wherever possible so suppressions are
#     revisited automatically when the date passes.
#   - Remove entries once the upstream package ships a fix and you have
#     upgraded to it.
#   - Never suppress CRITICAL findings without documented approval.
#
# Severity thresholds scanned in the pipeline: HIGH, CRITICAL
# =============================================================================

# Example entries (remove or replace with real findings):
#
# CVE-2023-12345   # false-positive in test dependency; not reachable in prod
# CVE-2022-98765 exp:2026-06-30  # vendor fix pending; reviewed 2026-03-24
